definition.value: A gamma-lactone resulting from the formal intramolecular condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of 2-hydroxyglutaric acid with the carboxy group at position 5.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (21Z,24Z,27Z,30Z)-hexatriacontatetraenoic acid.

A primary aliphatic amine that is butane in which one hydrogen at position 2 is replaced by an amino group. A fumigant fungicide with a high potential for bioaccumulation, it is not approved for fungicidal use in the European Union.
A dipeptide formed from L-leucine and beta-alanine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-leucine and D-leucine residues.
A role borne by a molecule that acts to counteract or neutralize the deleterious effects of paracetamol (acetaminophen).
A role borne by a molecule that acts to counteract or neutralize the deleterious effects of curare.
A dipeptide formed from L-leucine and L-glutamic acid residues.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the N-acyl group is specified as docosanoyl
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the N-acyl group is specified as (13Z)-docosenoyl.
A dipeptide formed from L-leucine and glycine residues.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the N-acyl group is specified as (15Z)-tetracosenoyl.
A thiol that is glycerol in which one of the primary hydroxy groups is replaced by a thiol group.
A tripeptide composed of one L-leucine and two glycine residues joined in sequence.
A dipeptide formed from L-leucine and L-histidine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-leucine and L-isoleucine residues.
A tripeptide formed from three L-leucine residues.
A beta-D-glucoside in which the anomeric substituent is specified as 2,2,2-trichloroethyl.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of 8-methyladenosine 5'-monophosphate residue.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.

An L-alpha-amino acid that is L-alanine in which the methyl group is replaced by a (5S)-3-chloro-4,5-dihydro-1,2-oxazol-5-yl group. A glutamine analogue antimetabolite, it interferes with glutamate metabolism and  several glutamate-dependent synthetic enzymes. It is obtained as a fermentation product of Streptomyces sviceus bacteria.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.

A 1-acyl-2-octadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-oleoyl-2-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.
A dipeptide formed from L-lysine and L-arginine residues.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-heptadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.
A ribonucleoside monophosphate that is tubercidin with a phosphate group replacing the hydrogen on the 5'-hydroxy group.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-heptadecanoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.
A dipeptide formed from L-lysine and L-glutamic acid residues.

A dipeptide formed from L-lysine and L-leucine residues.
A fatty amide derived from valproic acid.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-oleoyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.
A dipeptide formed from two L-lysine residues.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.
A dipeptide formed from L-lysine and L-methionine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-lysine and L-proline residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-lysine and L-serine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-lysine and L-tryptophan residues.
An EC 2.3.2.* (aminoacyltransferase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of gamma-glutamyltransferase (EC 2.3.2.2).
